method.name: UploadMission
method.comment: Uploads a mission. The Result event will be raised.

method.name: StartMission
method.comment: Starts a mission. The Result event will be raised.

method.name: Initialize
method.comment: Initializes the mission operator.

method.name: LoadMission
method.comment: Loads a mission. The next step is to upload it with UploadMission.

method.name: PauseMission
method.comment: Pauses a mission. The Result event will be raised.

method.name: ResumeMission
method.comment: Resumes a mission. The Result event will be raised.

method.name: StopMission
method.comment: Stops a mission. The Result event will be raised.

property.name: MissionState
property.comment: Returns the mission state. One of the following values: UNKNOWN, DISCONNECTED, NOT_SUPPORTED, RECOVERING, READY_TO_UPLOAD, UPLOADING, READY_TO_EXECUTE, EXECUTING, EXECUTION_PAUSED.

class.name: anywheresoftware.b4a.objects.WaypointMissionOperatorWrapper.WaypointMissionBuilderWrapper
class.comment: Mission builder. Note that the AutoFlightSpeed and MaxFlightSpeed must be set.

method.name: AddWaypoint
method.comment: Adds a waypoint.

method.name: SetFinishAction
method.comment: Action that will be executed when the mission finishes. NO_ACTION - No further action will be taken on completion of mission. GO_HOME - The aircraft will go home and land. AUTO_LAND - The aircraft will land at the last waypoint. GO_FIRST_WAYPOINT - The aircraft will go to the first waypoint. CONTINUE_UNTIL_END - Mission will not end until StopMission is called.

property.name: AutoFlightSpeed
property.comment: Gets or sets the auto flight speed (m/s). This is the default flight speed. Valid values are between -15 to 15.

property.name: MaxFlightSpeed
property.comment: Gets or sets the maximum flight speed (m/s). Maximum speed is achieved by pushing the throttle joystick.

method.name: Initialize
method.comment: Initializes the waypoint with the given coordinate and altitude (in meters).

method.name: AddAction
method.comment: Adds an action that will be executed when the aircraft reaches the point. Action - One of the following values: STAY - Stays at the current point. Parameter = Period in milliseconds. START_TAKE_PHOTO - Starts to shoot a photo. Parameter is ignored. START_RECORD - Starts recordsing. Parameter is ignored. STOP_RECORD - Stops recording. Parameter is ignored. ROTATE_AIRCRAFT - Rotates the aircraft's yaw. Parameter should be between -180 to 180. GIMBAL_PITCH - Rotates the gimbal's pitch. Parameter should be between -90 to 0.

method.name: SetGoHomeHeightInMeters
method.comment: Sets the go home flight height. Should be between 20 to 500. The Result event will be raised.

method.name: AutoLanding
method.comment: Starts an auto-landing action. The Result event will be raised. Returns an object that can be used as the sender filter parameter.

method.name: TakeOff
method.comment: Starts a takeoff action. The engine will start automatically. The Result event will be raised. Returns an object that can be used as the sender filter parameter.

method.name: Initialize
method.comment: Initializes the flight controller.

method.name: GoHomeStart
method.comment: Starts a go home action. The Result event will be raised.

method.name: SetHomeLocationUsingAircraftCurrentLocation
method.comment: Sets the home location based on the current aircraft location. The Result event will be raised. Example: Dim sf As Object = controller.SetHomeLocationUsingAircraftCurrentLocation Wait For (sf) Controller_Result (Success As Boolean, ErrorMessage As String) If Success Then Log("Home location set.") Else Log("Error: " & ErrorMessage) End If

method.name: GoHomeCancel
method.comment: Cancels a go home action. The Result event will be raised.

property.name: Heading
property.comment: Returns the aircraft heading.

property.name: CurrentState
property.comment: Returns the current state.

property.name: SimulatorStarted
property.comment: Returns true if the simulator has started.

property.name: GyroscopeState
property.comment: Returns one of the following values: UNKNOWN, DISCONNECTED, CALIBRATING, CALIBRATION_FAILED, DATA_EXCEPTION, WARMING_UP, IN_MOTION, NORMAL_BIAS, MEDIUM_BIAS, LARGE_BIAS.

property.name: CalibrationStatus
property.comment: Returns one of the following values: NONE, CALIBRATING, SUCCESSFUL, FAILED, UNKNOWN.

property.name: AccelerometerStatus
property.comment: Returns one of the following values: UNKNOWN, DISCONNECTED, CALIBRATING, CALIBRATION_FAILED, DATA_EXCEPTION, WARMING_UP, IN_MOTION, NORMAL_BIAS, MEDIUM_BIAS, LARGE_BIAS.

property.name: AircraftLocation
property.comment: Returns the aircraft location.

property.name: FlightMode
property.comment: Returns the current flight mode. Possible values: Manual, Atti, AttiCourseLock, AttiHover, Hover, GPSBlake, GPSAtti, GPSCourseLock, GPSHomeLock, GPSHotPoint, AssistedTakeOff, AutoTakeOff, AutoLanding, AttiLanding, GPSWaypoint, GoHome, ClickGo, Joystick, AttiLimited, GPSAttiLimited, GPSFollowMe, Tracking, Pointing, PANO, Farming, FPV, GPSSport, GPSNovice, ConfirmLanding, TerrainTracking, NaviAdvGoHome, NaviAdvLanding, TripodGPS, TrackHeadLock, MotorsJustStarted, GPSGentle, Unknown

property.name: Attitude
property.comment: Returns the aircraft attitude (pitch, roll and yaw).

property.name: AreMotorsOn
property.comment: Returns true if the motors are on.

property.name: GPSStatus
property.comment: Returns 255 if there is no signal. Otherwise returns a value between 0 (weak signal) to 5 (strong signal).

property.name: IMUPreheating
property.comment: Returns True if the IMU is preheating.

property.name: Flying
property.comment: Returns True if the aircraft is flying.

property.name: GoingHome
property.comment: Returns True if the aircraft is going home.

property.name: VelocityX
property.comment: Returns the x-axis velocity measured in meters per second.

property.name: SatelliteCount
property.comment: Returns the number of GPS satellites found.

property.name: HomeLocation
property.comment: Returns the home location.

property.name: HomeLocationSet
property.comment: Returns true if the home location was set.

property.name: GoHomeHeight
property.comment: Returns the go home height in meters.

property.name: VelocityZ
property.comment: Returns the z-axis velocity measured in meters per second.

property.name: VelocityY
property.comment: Returns the y-axis velocity measured in meters per second.

property.name: Altitude
property.comment: Returns the altitude measured by barometer in meters (relative to the take off location).
